1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:04,333
They released us at the time of the afternoon prayer

2
00:00:04,750 --> 00:00:07,208
They brought us to Hajj Idris Mosque

3
00:00:08,083 --> 00:00:09,625
Abd al-Rahman ibn Awf Mosque

4
00:00:09,708 --> 00:00:11,125
We went in and prayed the afternoon prayer

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,458
And they released us from the mosque

6
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:18,875
Interviewer: Did they treat you harshly?

7
00:00:18,916 --> 00:00:21,208
No, it was very ordinary treatment

8
00:00:21,208 --> 00:00:22,625
Interviewer: Where did you take your belongings from?

9
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,458
They gave us the belongings there

10
00:00:25,458 --> 00:00:29,041
My watch, my things, and my ID, and we left

11
00:00:30,375 --> 00:00:35,041
Interviewer: After you got out and were released and returned home

12
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:37,458
Did your family know you’d be released?

13
00:00:37,458 --> 00:00:38,458
No, they did not know

14
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:40,958
Interviewer: Can you describe how you felt?

15
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:45,500
And the moment your family met you, your wife and children?

16
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:47,750
It was an indescribable feeling

17
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:50,375
Interviewer: I want you to try to describe how it was

18
00:00:50,458 --> 00:00:54,625
I was very happy. I wanted to hug my children and my family

19
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:57,208
And my friends and my people

20
00:00:57,375 --> 00:01:00,458
And they all celebrated me

21
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:02,750
But it was a simple celebration

22
00:01:03,208 --> 00:01:05,333
So the noise would not be heard

23
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:08,958
Because they were not allowed to hear the sounds of ululations and celebration

24
00:01:09,625 --> 00:01:10,958
Interviewer: How was your meeting with your wife?

25
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,958
And with your mother who was still alive at the time?

26
00:01:13,625 --> 00:01:18,583
How did you feel in that meeting and was there crying from joy?

27
00:01:19,041 --> 00:01:20,083
Yes, there was crying from joy

28
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:24,000
My kids and my wife cried from joy

29
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,083
And they asked me at home—What did you do for them to take you?

30
00:01:30,458 --> 00:01:34,916
I told them, I did nothing, you are my family and you know what I have

31
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:36,750
They took me unjustly

32
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:40,333
And thank God, God made it easy for me and I was released
